Caepio (ξ 28).—Q. Servilius Caepio, praetor inc. 110, consul Bm. 106. The province of Gallia Narbonensis having been assigned to him, he captured and plundered the city of Tolosa, which had joined the Cimbri. The booty he thus obtained was immense, but in the following year, in consequence of a quarrel between him and the Consul Mallius, the Romans sustained at the hands of the Cimbri the most severe defeat they had ever suffered,—80‚OOO soldicrs and 40,000 camp sollowers were killed.
